                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "subtype": "monster_family"
                },
                "game-id": "e7670f7230450b64cdefbe8a640f70e1",
                "text": "While domesticated pigs are a staple of farm life, wild boars are much more dangerous. Foul-tempered warthogs are relatively common, while the lumbering, primeval beasts known as daeodons are less so. Voracious boars can ravage the countryside in which they live, making them a particular nuisance to farmers. Boars breed freely, and a pair of boars can rapidly grow to a large family.",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "link": {
                    "type": "link",
                    "name": "Boar",
                    "alt": "Boar",
                    "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
                    "aonid": 372
                }
            },
